
[1]proneness

   PRO'NENESS, n. The state of bending downwards; opposed to the erectness
   of man.

   1. The state of lying with the face downwards; contrary to supineness.

   2. Descent; declivity; as the proneness of a hill.

   3. Inclination of mind, heart or temper; propension; disposition; as
   the proneness of the Israelites to idolatry; proneness to
   self-gratification or to self-justification; proneness to comply with
   temptation; sometimes in a good sense; as ;the proneness of good men to
   commiserate want.
